  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd6\u0dbd\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dca \u0db4\u0dc4\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d88\u0dc0\u0dbb \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Five finance companies are liquidating",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Central Bank of Sri Lanka plans to liquidate five finance companies whose licenses have been revoked. Accordingly, Central Investment and Finance Limited, ETI Finance Limited, TKS Finance Limited, The Finance Company PLC and The Standard Credit Finance Limited are to be set up.",
        "Central Investment and Finance Limited Ltd., ETI Finance Ltd. Finance Ltd., The Finance Company PLC and The Standard Credit Finance Ltd. (5) formed a failed financing company revival advisory committee (Consultative Advisory Committee) to examine possible alternative proposals for revival (5). .",
        "The Monetary Board had tasked this Advisory Committee to make possible alternative recommendations for the revival of the above 5 failed finance companies or to make recommendations for the liquidation of the five (5) failed finance companies if such viable alternatives are not feasible. .",
        "The Advisory Committee submitted its final report to the Monetary Board on 31.05.2022 after scrutinizing several proposals submitted by various parties regarding four (4) of the aforementioned failed finance companies.",
        "The Monetary Board, after considering the report of the Advisory Committee on the five (5) failed finance companies, said that the proposals made to the Advisory Committee would create policy and legal issues and that those proposals could not be implemented in practice within the existing legal framework. Noted.",
        "Further, the Advisory Committee expects that no proposals will be put forward by prospective investors that can be put into practice in the current economic climate. Under these circumstances, out of the above five (5) failed finance companies, the only option is to continue the liquidation of the finance companies which have already applied for liquidation and to apply for liquidation of the finance companies which have not so requested.",
        "In view of the above, the report of the Advisory Committee recommended the dissolution of that Committee. Based on the recommendation of the Advisory Committee, the Monetary Board decided to dissolve the Advisory Committee.",
        "Accordingly, action will be taken in future to liquidate the five (5) failed finance companies in accordance with the relevant legal provisions."
      ],
